[Lowland forests in secondary and disturbed areas up to elevations of ¢. 
<quantity id="4CFC9B09FFCDF62380D838C4F587F36E" box="[2502,2594,3288,3317]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFCDF6238C6C38E7F5B3F287" box="[1394,2582,3323,3356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="67" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFCDF6238C6C38E7F5B3F287" blockId="9.[1392,2604,2024,3474]" box="[1394,2582,3323,3356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFCDF6238C6C38E7F9DDF287" bold="true" box="[1394,1656,3323,3356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="67">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFCDF6238FDB38E7F822F287" authorityName="Kitchener &amp; Maharadatunkamsi" authorityYear="1991" box="[1733,1927,3323,3356]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Cynopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nusatenggara">Nusatenggara</taxonomicName>
Short-nosed Fruit Bat is primarily frugivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
